extends ../layout

block content
  .d-flex.flex-column.mb-5
    p.lead.text-center
      | My BYOB (bring your own beamer) generative art projects. These are interactive installations
      | that transform real-time data into flowing visual experiences using WebGL and particle systems.

    .d-flex.gap-2.mb-3.justify-content-center
      a.btn(href="https://nerdlab.be/byob" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="background-color: white; color: #333; border: 1px solid #ddd;")
        img(src="/images/logos/nerdlab-glasses.svg" alt="Nerdlab" style="height: 20px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: middle;")
        |  BYOB Event

  .row.mb-4
    .col-lg-6.mb-4.mb-lg-0
      .card.h-100
        .card-body
          h5.card-title Flow Viz
          .d-flex.gap-2.mb-3
            a.btn(href="https://mateovandamme.github.io/flow-viz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="background-color: #2196F3; color: white; border: none;") Live Demo
            a.btn(href="https://github.com/MateoVanDamme/flow-viz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="background-color: #333; color: white; border: none;")
              svg(xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" style="margin-right: 6px;")
                path(d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.012 8.012 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z")
              | GitHub
          p.card-text.mb-3
            | A real-time generative artwork that transforms ambient sound into flowing rivers of light.
            | Uses live microphone input to analyze frequencies and drive 50,000 particles across the screen.
          .feature-list
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label Bass frequencies
              span  → wave patterns
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label Mid-range sounds
              span  → turbulence effects
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label High frequencies
              span  → chaotic energy bursts
          p.card-text.small.text-muted.mt-3
            | Built with WebGL and JavaScript. Each viewing experience is unique based on the ambient sonic environment.

    .col-lg-6.mb-4.mb-lg-0
      .card.h-100
        .card-body
          h5.card-title Flow Field
          .d-flex.gap-2.mb-3
            a.btn(href="https://mateovandamme.github.io/flow-field/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="background-color: #2196F3; color: white; border: none;") Live Demo
            a.btn(href="https://github.com/MateoVanDamme/flow-field" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="background-color: #333; color: white; border: none;")
              svg(xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16" style="margin-right: 6px;")
                path(d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.012 8.012 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z")
              | GitHub
          p.card-text.mb-3
            | An interactive particle visualization where edges detected in your camera feed guide 50,000 particles to float along them.
            | When no edges are present, the particles follow organic Perlin noise patterns. All edge detection runs on the GPU in real-time.
          .feature-list
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label 50,000 particles
              span  following flow fields
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label Sobel edge detection
              span  processed on GPU
            .feature-item
              span.feature-label Real-time webcam
              span  influence on particle flow
          p.card-text.small.text-muted.mt-3
            | Built with Three.js. Press "D" to toggle control panels. Requires webcam permission for full functionality.

  style.
    .feature-list {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .feature-item {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .feature-label {
      color: #2196F3;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
